04/06/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Paddy Ashdown appointed 16 members of the BiH High Judicial and Prosecutorial Council (HJPC) on Thursday (3 June). 
Nine have already served with the Council. 
The establishment of a single HJPC is a requirement for opening negotiations on signing a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with BiH.
Also Thursday, the BiH State Border Service (SBS) started celebrations marking its fourth anniversary with a special ceremony in Sarajevo. 
BiH presidency Chairman Sulejman Tihic described the establishment of SBS as one of the most successful projects aimed at strengthening the rule of law in BiH thus far. 
(Fena, NTV Hayat, PBS BiH - 03/06/04)
